circumstances.circumstancesOfRecovery: The Jane Doe was found in 2004 at Ala Moana Beach Park in Oahu and transferred to Kauai to live out her days in the state hospital, Mahelona. She had no memory of who she was or any other details regarding her life. She died on April 27, 2013 without discovering her identity. Her name and origin are unknown, but she sometimes referred to herself as Ah or Pansie which is believed to be both aliases. She also spoke with an accent which was undetermined. It is believed that she has been in Hawaii since 1994.
